# Course Manager — Full Redesign Implementation Plan

## Background & Goal

The Course Manager becomes the **central academic hub** of The ANTs. A student sets up their courses once, and every other feature — Lesson Tracker, Exam Countdowns, Notes, and Flashcards — automatically adapts to show only relevant content for their selected curricula and subjects.

---

## Resolved Decisions

| # | Question | Decision |
|---|---|---|
| 1a | Countdown scope per subject | **Single next upcoming session** (`exam_date > NOW()` ORDER BY date ASC LIMIT 1). User can manually switch to a later session via a dropdown on the card. |
| 1b | Subject → Exam lookup logic | **Only auto-generate if a concrete `exams` table record exists** for that `subject_id`. If no match: show a friendly placeholder UI ("Timetable not released yet — we'll update this automatically"). No fake countdowns. |
| 2 | `useLessons` hook | **Delete it.** Replace all usages with `useLessonContext()`. Eliminates duplicate Supabase queries. |
| 3 | Filter persistence | **`localStorage`** — selected curriculum/subject filters persist across page refreshes and new browser tabs. |
| 4 | Mock flashcard data | **Auto-migrate** via a one-shot script. Reads mock `decks` + `cards` from `lib/mock/database.ts` and upserts them into Supabase. No manual work needed. |

