## Database Analysis — No New Tables Required

The existing schema fully supports all 5 user flows:

```
curriculums  ──┐
               ├──> subjects ──> topics
               │          └──> exams (subject_id FK)
               └──> notes (curriculum_id + subject_id FKs)

user_enrollments (user_id, curriculum_id, subject_id, exam_id?)
topic_progress   (user_id, topic_id, status, confidence_level)
exam_countdowns  (user_id, exam_id, target_date, custom_title, qualification_group)
decks            (owner_id, curriculum_id, subject_id, name, is_public)
cards            (deck_id, front_text, back_text)
```

All reads use the `authenticated` role with `user_id = auth.uid()` predicates. Public tables (`curriculums`, `subjects`, `topics`, `exams`) are already readable by all authenticated users.

