#### [NEW] `scripts/migrate-mock-decks.ts`

One-shot migration script. Run once during implementation.

```ts
// Pseudocode:
import { mockDecks, mockCards } from '../src/lib/mock/database';
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js';

const supabase = createClient(SUPABASE_URL, SERVICE_ROLE_KEY);

// Upsert decks
await supabase.from('decks').upsert(
  mockDecks.map(d => ({
    id: d.id, owner_id: d.owner_id, name: d.name,
    description: d.description, category: d.category,
    curriculum_id: d.curriculum_id, subject_id: d.subject_id,
    is_public: d.is_public, created_at: d.created_at,
  })),
  { onConflict: 'id' }
);

// Upsert cards
await supabase.from('cards').upsert(
  mockCards.map(c => ({
    id: c.id, deck_id: c.deck_id,
    front_text: c.front_text, back_text: c.back_text,
    created_at: c.created_at,
  })),
  { onConflict: 'id' }
);
```

Logs success/failure per batch. After running, the mock functions in `DeckLibrary` and `CreateDeckModal` can be fully replaced.

